  "local_port": 40568,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "Configuring a universal remote can be straightforward by following these steps. Here's a structured guide to help you:\n\n### **Preparation**\n- **Gather Information**: Note the brands and model numbers of your devices (TV, soundbar, etc.).\n- **Check Batteries**: Ensure the remote has fresh batteries.\n- **Power On Devices**: Turn on the device you want to program (e.g., TV).\n\n---\n\n### **Method 1: Auto-Search (Code Scanning)**\n1. **Enter Setup Mode**:\n   - Press and hold the **Setup** button (or device-specific button like \"TV\") until the remote\u2019s light blinks.\n2. **Initiate Auto-Search**:\n   - Press the **Power** button once.\n   - Repeatedly press the **Volume Up** (or another designated) button. The remote will cycle through codes.\n3. **Save the Code**:\n   - When the device turns off, immediately press the **Setup** (or device) button to lock in the code.\n4. **Test Functions**: Check power, volume, and input buttons.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Manual Code Entry**\n1. **Find Codes**:\n   - Check the remote\u2019s manual, manufacturer\u2019s website, or online databases for codes.\n2. **Enter Code**:\n   - Press **Setup**, then enter the 3-5 digit code using the keypad. The light may blink to confirm.\n3. **Test**: If the device turns off/on, the code works. If not, repeat with another code.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 3: App Configuration (Smart Remotes)**\n1. **Download App**: Install the manufacturer\u2019s app (e.g., Logitech Harmony, Broadlink).\n2. **Pair Remote**: Connect the remote via Bluetooth/Wi-Fi as instructed.\n3. **Select Devices**: Follow in-app steps to add your devices.\n\n---\n\n### **Alternative: Learning Mode**\n1. **Enable Learning**:\n   - Press **Setup** \u2192 select \"Learning\" or \"Program\" mode.\n2. **Teach Commands**:\n   - Point the original remote at the universal remote and press buttons to copy them.\n\n---\n\n### **Troubleshooting**\n- **No Response**: Check line of sight, replace batteries, or reset the remote (see manual).\n- **Partial Functionality**: Try alternate codes or use learning mode for missing buttons.\n- **Reset**: Use a paperclip to press the reset button (if available) or remove batteries for 1 minute.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n- **Online Resources**: Manufacturer websites often have updated code lists.\n- **Customer Support**: Contact the remote\u2019s support team for help.\n- **Test All Buttons**: Ensure volume, input, and settings work post-setup.\n\nBy following these steps, you can configure most universal remotes efficiently. If issues persist, consult your remote\u2019s manual for model-specific guidance.",
